<pdfbody>
    <div style="height: 0.8cm;">
        &nbsp;
    </div><br>

    <table class="w-100">
        <tr style="font-weight: bold;">
            <td style="width: 3.5em;">Ref No</td>
            <td>: <%= @data[:ref_number] %></td>
        </tr>

        <tr style="font-weight: bold;">
            <td style="width: 3.5em;">Date</td>
            <td>: <%= raw @data[:letter_date] %></td>
        </tr>

        <tr>
            <td colspan="2"><%= simple_format @letter.employer_address %></td>
        </tr>
    </table>

    <p>Dear Sir/Madam,</p>

    <p class="letter-header-underline"><b><%= @data[:letter_title] %></b></p>

    <p class="text-justify">
       This is with reference to the above matter. The chest X-ray examination of the below foreign worker was reported as NORMAL chest x-ray findings by the x-ray facility.
    </p>

    <p class="text-justify">
        Foreign worker&apos;s particulars are as follows:
    </p>

    <table class="w-100" border="1px" style="border-collapse: collapse; text-align: center;">
        <tr>
            <td valign="top" style="width: 8em; background-color: #D3D3D3;"><b>WORKER CODE</b></td>
            <td valign="top" style="width: 8em; background-color: #D3D3D3;"><b>NAME</b></td>
            <td valign="top" style="width: 8em; background-color: #D3D3D3;"><b>PASSPORT NUMBER</b></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><%= @letter.worker_code %></td>
            <td><%= @letter.worker_name %></td>
            <td><%= @letter.worker_passport %></td>
        </tr>
    </table>

    <p class="text-justify">
        However, on subsequent auditing of the chest x-ray by our consultant radiologist, the chest x-ray findings have been confirmed as <b>ABNORMAL</b>. For your information, the auditing of chest x-ray is part of our quality control in the chest x-ray examination.
    </p>
    <p class="text-justify">
        In view of the matter above, the worker&apos;s  medical status has now been amended to <b>UNSUITABLE</b> for employment in Malaysia. The foreign worker should return to his/her country of origin.
    </p>
    <p class="text-justify">
        Thank you
    </p>

    <!-- This is the only way to keep this entire block together. For some reason, page-break-inside: avoid; does not work -->
    <table style="margin-left: -2px;">
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: 0;">
                <p style="margin: 0;">
                    Yours sincerely,<br><br><br><br><br>
                    <b><%= @letter.issuer_name %></b><br>
                    <%= @letter.issuer_title %>
                </p>
            </td>
        </tr>
    </table>
</pdfbody>

<style>
    pdfbody {
        font-size: 18px; /* Was originally 16px */
    }

    .w-100 {
        width: 100%;
    }

    .letter-header-underline {
        display: inline;
        border-bottom: 2px solid black;
    }

    .text-justify {
        text-align: justify;
    }
</style>